          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For  protons  - plastic scintillator hodoscope",
                " PiP with ~ 1 sr solid angle,  covering proton  polar",
                " angle from 50 to 130 deg  and  azimuthal  angles  of",
                " 13.5 - 22 deg.",
                "Correlated protons and neutrons were detected in TOF,",
                " an array of plastic scintillator detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors.",
                "There are  several  sources  of  possible  systematic",
                " error. Uncertainties in the detection of neutrons in",
                " TOF arise   from  the  calculation  of  the  neutron",
                " detection efficiency (10 %) and  from  uncertainties",
                " in TOF  neutron  detection  thresholds  (5  %).  The",
                " contribution to the charged particle  yield  in  TOF",
                " due to  neutral particles in random coincidence with",
                " signal from deltaE  detectors  near  the  target  is",
                " generally small, except at most forward angles where",
                " it can be as much as 10 %.  The TOF proton detection",
                " efficiency rise to an uncertainty of 3 %  in the TOF",
                " proton yield.  The uncertainty  in  the  PiP  proton",
                " detection efficiency  is 3 %.  Further uncertainties",
                " occur in the determination of the  target  thickness",
                " (1 %) and the photon polarization (5 %)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photon  asymmatry  of  the 12C(g-pol,pn) reaction",
                " has been  measured  for  separate   missing   energy",
                " regions corresponding  to  the  ejection of nucleons",
                " from (1p)**2 and (1p)(1s) shells."
              ]
            }
          ],
